# Part 2: Making a small simulation
tldr: talk about the basics of conway's game of life
then the changes from botania,

let it run all night, no final results, notice multiplication error
relaunch, finishes in under a few minutes! doesn't give quite an optimal solution sadly...
Optimizing time, bong bonk bomg and boom, padded game grid to avoid branching, hitting cache is faster than branching
hardcoding some offset values, comptime inlining some easy loops
BAM done in under minute for more random searches.

# Part 3: Parallelizing the simulation
tldr: with the simulation working, we just needed to take this bad boy and drop it into multiple threads.... why are we getting the same results?
Oh yeah, seed for the randomizer, well, let's pass a different seed for each simulation, fix some more bugs that I didn't notice.

BADABIM BADABOOM, we now got 12 threads on my 5 5600 doing some really good work, but well just getting 1 setup from a single thread, not so great.

# Part 4: More flowers per thread
Change from single winner to top 10 winners, and now we're getting some really good results, but still not great.

Wait, friend mentioned something about genetic algorithms and minor alterations to existing setups to see if it performs better or worse overall
.... 

# Part 5: Genetic Algorithms
And many bugs later, we now can mutate a game board inital state and merge two game boards together as if they are genetic strands. Suprisingly, this does actually help improve the score a lot higher than I saw with just random change

# Part 6: Now we are slow again
Since I wasn't quite getting the results I wanted and I didn't perfect the genetic algorithm yet while waiting on feedback, I decided to do the smartest things ever. increase the sample size of random flowers we generated from about 10000 to 1000000.

Cpu is taking long, not long enough to push to another solution but slow enough I am not happy. But results were barely improving.

So naturally I just though, what if I just add more flowers? Clearly the smart thing to do! Cpu is slow though that'll kill me.... Well... There is another device on this pc.... Gpu-chan... shall we dance? 

Now I am reading Vulkan, I feel like once I finish this, I could built a plan with my bare hands. VULKAN IS GRANTING ME ENDLESS POWER.

